        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "🧠 1️⃣ SUBJECT PRONOUNS (कर्ता)"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "👉 Sentence में action करने वाला।"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "I play.",
                "She is smart.",
                "They are here."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>कर्ता मतलब work कौन करता है।"
        },
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "🎯 2️⃣ OBJECT PRONOUNS (कर्म)"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "👉 Action जिसे मिलता है / Preposition के बाद आता है।"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "He called me.",
                "I will help them.",
                "Give it to her."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>Verb के बाद हमेशा object आता है।"
        },
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "🏠 3️⃣ POSSESSIVE ADJECTIVES"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "👉 बाद में noun आता है।"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "This is my book.",
                "That is their car."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>Ownership + Noun combo."
        },
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "🔑 4️⃣ POSSESSIVE PRONOUNS (Noun नहीं आता)"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "👉 mine, yours, his, hers, ours, theirs"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "This book is mine.",
                "The house is theirs."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>Ownership alone."
        },
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "🪞 5️⃣ REFLEXIVE PRONOUNS"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "👉 Action अपने ऊपर → myself, yourself, himself…"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "I hurt myself.",
                "They enjoyed themselves."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>Doer & receiver same."
        },
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "🫱🏼‍🫲🏻 6️⃣ RECIPROCAL PRONOUNS"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "👉 दो लोग → each other<br/>👉 कई → one another"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "Twins love each other.",
                "Students help one another."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "⚖️ 7️⃣ 231 RULE (Order of Pronouns)"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "👉 Positive sentence → You → He/She → I"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "✔ **Correct:** You, he and I will go.",
                "❌ **Wrong:** I, you and he will go."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "content": "💡 **Why?**<br/>Respect order → 2 → 3 → 1"
        },
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "🪫 8️⃣ Preposition के बाद Object Case"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "👉 between, to, for, with… के बाद → me, him, her, us, them"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "✔ **Examples:**",
                "between you and me",
                "with him",
                "for them",
                "❌ **Wrong:** between you and I"
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "🌧 9️⃣ “IT” का सही उपयोग"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "👉 Weather, time, distance, animal, thing"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "It is raining.",
                "It is 4 PM.",
                "I have a cat. It is cute."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "🏁 🔟 Comparison Rule (than/as)"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "👉 Formal → Subject Case<br/>👉 Informal → Object Case"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "✔ **Formal:** He is taller than I (am).",
                "✔ **Spoken:** He is taller than me."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "📝 1️⃣1️⃣ Pronoun + Noun Rule"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "👉 Pronoun हमेशा noun से पहले"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "✔ **Examples:**",
                "We students will speak.",
                "You boys come here.",
                "❌ **Wrong:** Students we will speak."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "🧍‍♂️🧍‍♀️ 1️⃣2️⃣ Gender-Neutral “They”"
